@DeFiVet This is super helpful! Quick follow-up on the liquidity calculation:

```solidity
uint256 liquidity = Math.sqrt(amountA * amountB);
```

Why use square root here? I've seen other implementations use different formulas. Is this the Uniswap V2 approach?

Also, for initial liquidity provision, how do you handle the case where someone provides very unbalanced amounts (like 1000:1 ratio)? Won't this mess up the price discovery?
